In [40]:
def plots(df, var, t):
    plt.figure(figsize = (13,5))
    plt.subplot(121)
    sns.kdeplot(df[var])
    plt.title('Before '+ str(t))
    
    plt.subplot(122)
    p1 = t.fit_transform(df[[var]]).flatten()
    sns.kdeplot(p1)
    plt.title('After '+ str(t))
    
for x in numeric_features:
    if ((df[x] <= 0).values.any()==False):
        plots(df, x, PowerTransformer(method='box-cox'))
    else:
        plots(df, x, PowerTransformer(method='yeo-johnson'))
        
#After looking at these results, the power transformer doesn't seem to benefit the data, for that reason we will leave it 
#out. We will simply apply standard scaler

from sklearn.metrics import confusion_matrix, classification_report, accuracy_score, recall_score, precision_score

# # Predicting on the testing data and printing the R2 score and MSLE metrics

def conf_matrix(model):
    classes = ['Converted', 'Demented', 'Non-demented']
    prediction = model.predict(x_test)
    y_pred = np.argmax(prediction, axis = 1)
    y_true = np.argmax(y_test_cat, axis = 1)
    accuracy = accuracy_score(y_true, y_pred)
    recall = recall_score(y_true, y_pred, average = None)
    precision = precision_score(y_true, y_pred, average = None)
    print('Recall: ', recall, '\n Accuracy: ', accuracy, '\n Precision: ',precision)
    clf_rpt = classification_report(y_true, y_pred)
    print("classification report :\n", clf_rpt)
    cm = confusion_matrix(y_pred, y_true)
    sns.heatmap(cm,annot=True)
    plt.xticks(np.arange(3) + .5, labels = classes)
    plt.yticks(np.arange(3) + .5, labels = classes)
    plt.xlabel('True')
    plt.ylabel('Predicted')
   
    return recall, accuracy, precision

def conf_matrixml(model):
    classes = ['Converted', 'Demented', 'Non-demented']
    prediction = model.predict(X_test)
    accuracy = accuracy_score(y_test, prediction)
    recall = recall_score(y_test, prediction, average = None)
    precision = precision_score(y_test, prediction, average = None)
    print('Recall: ', recall, '\n Accuracy: ', accuracy, '\n Precision: ',precision)
    clf_rpt = classification_report(y_test, prediction)
    print("classification report :\n", clf_rpt)
    cm = confusion_matrix(prediction, y_test)
    sns.heatmap(cm,annot=True)
    plt.xticks(np.arange(3) + .5, labels = classes)
    plt.yticks(np.arange(3) + .5, labels = classes)
    plt.xlabel('True')
    plt.ylabel('Predicted')
   
    return recall, accuracy, precision

In [48]:
def plot_model(history):
    fig,(ax1,ax2)=plt.subplots(1,2,figsize=(12,4))
    fig.suptitle('Model Accuracy and Loss')

    ax1.plot(history.history['accuracy'])
    ax1.plot(history.history['val_accuracy'])
    ax1.title.set_text('Accuracy')
    ax1.set_ylabel('Accuracy')
    ax1.set_xlabel('Epoch')
    ax1.legend(['Train','Valid'],loc=4)
    ax1.set_ylim([0, 1.3])

    ax2.plot(history.history['loss'])
    ax2.plot(history.history['val_loss'])
    ax2.title.set_text('Loss')
    ax2.set_ylabel('Loss')
    ax2.set_xlabel('Epoch')
    ax2.legend(['Train','Valid'],loc=1)
    ax2.set_ylim([0, 1.3])
    
    fig.show()

In [51]:
def create_baseline():
    n_features, n_outputs = X_train.shape[1], 3
    model = Sequential()
    model.add(Conv1D(filters=64, kernel_size=2, activation='relu', input_shape=(n_features,1)))
    model.add(Conv1D(filters=64, kernel_size=2, activation='relu'))
    model.add(Dropout(0.4))
    # dropout to prevent overfitting
    model.add(MaxPooling1D(pool_size=2))
    model.add(Flatten())
    model.add(Dense(100, activation='relu'))
    model.add(Dense(n_outputs, activation='softmax'))
    model.compile(loss='categorical_crossentropy', optimizer='adam', metrics=['accuracy'])
    return model
